THE matric results anxiety starts to set in for most grade
12 pupils. Some pupils say they are starting to have less sleep as they
think of how they might have performed. The SA depression and anxiety group has advised pupils who
feel anxious and overwhelmed to call in for counseling. Last year a total of 753964 full-time and 167915 registered
for 2022 matric exams. The exams were written in 6307 centres. Last year's matric exams were not without hiccups. Some pupils in Phandimfundo high school in Etwatwa had to
skip writing an Economics paper after their principal told them not to report
to school after allegedly telling them to stay home as there was going to be a
service delivery protest in the area. The grade 12 had to write the paper on 7 December. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments Cheating was also rife in 2022 matric exams. About 1189 grade 12 pupils were allegedly involved in
cheating. The Department of Basic Education had since launched an
investigation into these allegations. About 1127 pupils were allegedly from Mpumalanga schools. Pupils allegedly paid teachers up to R1500 to join WhatsApp
groups where answers were posted while exams were in session. Anxious matrics who need counseling can call SA Depression
and Anxiety group on these numbers from 8am to 8pm and speak to a counselor:
011 234 4837 / Fax Number: 011 234 8182 and a 24hr Helpline: 0800 456 789  